headline: This Absurdly Cheap Retail Stock Has Shrunk to Just 5% of Walmart's Value
summary: One of Walmart's biggest rivals, Target, isn't looking so big anymore and is just a fraction of its size.  Walmart has typically been more valuable than Target, but the gap has widened significantly.  As interest rates rose in 2022, investors appear to have dumped Target's stock in favor of Walmart.
